{
  "texts": [
    "6) Domain RandomizationWe use domain randomization [34] to improve robustness of the expert policies for sim-to-real transfer.",
    "First, friction coefficients and robot base mass are sampled using a uniform distribution from predefined ranges at the beginning of each episode.",
    "Second, push disturbances are simulated for quadruped training by adding a randomly sampled velocity to the robot base every 𝑇 -'*# seconds.",
    "Third, random noise is added to the proprioceptive observations o -245 and the actions 𝑎.",
    "Fourth, random motor delays are added to the action execution."
  ]
}